### [Proverbs Chapter 12](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 12:6](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">pro 12:6</span></span>

Lie in wait - Are designed to entrap others, and to destroy them.
Deliver them - From those that lie in wait for them.

[Proverbs 12:7](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">pro 12:7</span></span>

Are not - Both they and their families suddenly perish.

[Proverbs 12:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 12:9</span></span>

Despised - That lives in a mean condition. Honoureth - That glories in
his high birth or gay attire.

[Proverbs 12:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 12:10</span></span>

Regardeth - He will not destroy it either by labour beyond its strength,
or by denying it necessary food or rest. Cruel - There is cruelty mixed
even with their most merciful actions.

[Proverbs 12:11](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">pro 12:11</span></span>

Tilleth - That employs his time in an honest calling. Vain persons - In
an idle course of living.

[Proverbs 12:12](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">pro 12:12</span></span>

Desireth - He approves those arts, which wicked men use like nets to
ensnare other men. The root - That piety, which is the root of his
actions, yields him sufficient fruit both for his own need, and to do
good to others.

[Proverbs 12:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 12:14</span></span>

Mouth - By his pious and profitable discourses. Hands - Of his actions.

[Proverbs 12:15](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">pro 12:15</span></span>

Hearkeneth - That distrusts his own judgments, and seeks counsel from
others.

[Proverbs 12:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">pro 12:16</span></span>

Covereth - The shame, or injury done to him, which he conceals and bears
with patience.

[Proverbs 12:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 12:17</span></span>

Deceit - He who uses himself to lying in his common talk, will use
falsehood and deceit in judgment.

[Proverbs 12:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 12:18</span></span>

Health - Tends to the comfort and benefit of others.

[Proverbs 12:19](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">pro 12:19</span></span>

A moment - Liars, though they may make a fair shew for a season, yet are
quickly convicted.

[Proverbs 12:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 12:20</span></span>

Deceit - They whose hearts devise mischief shall be deceived in their
hopes, and bring trouble upon themselves: but they who by good counsels
labour to promote peace, shall reap the comfort of it themselves.

[Proverbs 12:23](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#023.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">pro 12:23</span></span>

Concealeth - He does not unseasonably utter what he knows. Foolishness -
Betrays his ignorance and folly.

[Proverbs 12:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">pro 12:25</span></span>

A good word - A compassionate or encouraging word.

[Proverbs 12:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 12:26</span></span>

Neighbour - Than any other men. Seduceth - Heb. maketh them to err, to
lose that excellency or happiness which they had promised themselves.

[Proverbs 12:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro012.htm#027.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_027">pro 12:27</span></span>

Resteth not - Does not enjoy the fruit of his labours. Precious - Yields
him comfort and blessing with it.

